w to reveal the weaknesses inherent in the Enlightenment system. Finally, Castrucci applies the theories of Carl Schmitt to the philosophical rationalism of the Western tradition, showing us how it has failed to contain absolute power in a juridical sense.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJurisprudencexHistory. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 0aLegislative powerxHistory. 0aPower (Christian theology) 0aPower (Christian theology). 0aPower (Philosophy) 0aPower (Philosophy). 0aPower (Social sciences) 0aPower (Social sciences). 4aLaw. 7aLAW / Jurisprudence.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311078044440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474411868?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474411868423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474411868/original  a978-3-11-078044-4  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK